---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Sojorn" description="Sojorn Privacy & Data Sovereignty Policy">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Privacy & Data Sovereignty</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p class="lead font-semibold">Profiting from surveillance is strictly against our principles. We reject the "attention economy" model and will never sell your data or allow third parties to track you.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">1. Data Sovereignty</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We do not sell your data. We do not license your data. We do not provide your data to third-party analytics, advertising, or data brokerage firms. Your content is not indexed on public search engines. Sojorn is a private community designed to protect your posts and identity from the extractivist economy.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">2. What We Collect</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We collect only what is technically necessary to operate the Service: your email address (authentication), birth month &amp; year (age verification), display name &amp; handle (profile identity), content you create (displayed to your chosen audience), approximate location for Beacons only (ephemeral), and device push tokens (notifications). We do <strong>not</strong> collect precise GPS location outside of Beacons, contact lists, browsing history, biometric data, or financial information.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We use Firebase (authentication, push notifications), Cloudflare R2 (media storage), SendPulse (newsletter delivery, opt-in only), and OpenAI / Google Vision (content moderation on public posts only). We do <strong>not</strong> use third-party tracking pixels, cross-site cookies, behavioral analytics, or third-party advertising SDKs.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">4. Zero-Knowledge Encryption</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Private messages and encrypted capsule content are protected by end-to-end encryption (E2EE) using keys generated on your device. <strong>We cannot decrypt your private content.</strong></p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">5. Your Right to Vanish</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You have the absolute right to delete your account and all associated data at any time. We perform <strong>hard deletes</strong> — database records, media files, and encryption key backups are permanently removed. We do not retain shadow copies, hidden archives, or behavioral profiles. When you leave, you leave.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">Automated cloud backups (Cloudflare R2) are retained for up to <strong>14 days</strong> as part of standard disaster-recovery operations. After that window, all backup data is permanently purged. Deletion requests take effect immediately in production systems; residual backup copies are removed as they age out of the retention window.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">6. Your Right to Clear Data</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You may request that some or all of your content be deleted without closing your account. This includes posts, messages, media, and activity history. You can submit a request through the app or via our <a href="/settings/clear-data" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">data clearing request form</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">7. Advertising &amp; In-App Data</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn may display sponsored content to help fund the platform. All advertising is served in-house by MPLS LLC. We do not use third-party ad networks, tracking pixels, or advertising SDKs. The factors that determine which ads you see include: your geographic neighborhood zone, the content section you are browsing, interest categories you explicitly choose, and your in-app engagement (such as likes and saves). This engagement data stays within Sojorn and is <strong>never shared with advertisers or any third party</strong>.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">You can disable engagement-based ad relevance in your settings at any time. You can also change or clear your declared interest categories. Advertisers receive only aggregate metrics (total impressions, total taps) — never user-level data, device information, or demographics.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">Content moderation logs (such as AI moderation decisions) retain content snippets for <strong>14 days</strong> to support the appeal process, after which snippets are permanently erased. Moderation metadata (scores, decisions) is retained for platform safety.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content is clearly labeled and subject to the same AI moderation and community guidelines as all other content. For complete details, see our <a href="/advertising" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">Advertising Policy</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">8. Anti-Extraction Commitment</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">MPLS LLC will never use your content to train AI models, sell or share your data with data brokers or third-party advertisers, export your engagement data outside of Sojorn, or provide "data partnerships" derived from your content or activity.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">9. Open Source Transparency</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Our source code is published under the <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">GNU Affero General Public License v3.0</a> (AGPL-3.0). We share our code so that users, security researchers, and the public can verify that we honor every commitment in this document. Our source code repository is hosted at <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">10. Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">For privacy concerns: <a href="mailto:privacy@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">privacy@sojorn.net</a>.<br>
        For legal inquiries: <a href="mailto:legal@mp.ls" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">legal@mp.ls</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
